## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words — Dense, firm, unyielding at low impact, deeply satisfying at high impact.
    - Feedback — Very direct and clear. You know exactly where on the racket you struck the ball.
    - Hold vs. Release — Exhibits a distinct hold only when you hit hard enough to penetrate the topsheet. Otherwise, it feels like a quick release.
    - Dwell Time — Moderate. It relies more on the topsheet's friction than deep sponge sinkage unless you swing with maximum power.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a muted, meaty thwack rather than a loud, metallic Tensor click. The sound is directly proportional to your effort.

