## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon — Great for aggressive blockers and flat hitters, but the combined stiffness can make looping very difficult for all but elite players.
    - Inner Carbon — The ideal match. The slight flex of an inner ALC/ZLC blade provides the necessary dwell time to activate the hard Bluestar A1 sponge.
    - All-Wood — Pairs well with stiff 7-ply all-wood blades (like Clipper wood) for a classic, heavy-spin game, though top-end speed might drop slightly.
    - Mismatch Cases — Avoid soft 5-ply all-wood blades; the setup will feel disconnected, heavy, and extremely demanding on your arm.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand — The primary domain for Bluestar A1. It perfectly supports the full-body mechanics and power required for modern forehand attacks.
    - Backhand — Recommended only for advanced-to-pro players with incredibly explosive backhand strokes. For most, it is too hard and heavy for backhand use.

